INTRODUCTION — MLP FOR XOR (DETAILED)
🔹 What is MLP?

👉 A Multilayer Perceptron (MLP) is an advanced neural network consisting of:

Input layer
Hidden layer(s)
Output layer

It can solve non-linear problems using activation functions and backpropagation.

🔹 Why XOR needs MLP?

👉 XOR is not linearly separable

This means:
❌ A single line cannot separate the classes

So:
✔ Perceptron fails
✔ MLP works (because of hidden layer)

🔹 How MLP solves XOR?

👉 MLP transforms input using hidden layer into a space where it becomes separable.

🔹 Working of MLP
Forward Pass
Input → Hidden → Output
Apply activation (sigmoid)
Error Calculation
Compare predicted vs actual
Backpropagation
Propagate error backward
Weight Update


Adjust weights to reduce error
